parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A fuel system leak or failure can cause a strong gasoline smell, and in severe cases, lead to a vehicle fire, which can result in serious injury or death.
symptoms: Strong gasoline smell
fuel dripping onto the manifold
fuel hose not staying connected to the line
oil leak (misdiagnosed).

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the turn signal module can cause the turn signals to malfunction, leading to reduced visibility and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: The turn signals do not function properly
the headlights and/or parking lights malfunction
the power door locks do not function correctly
the rear brakes malfunction.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel injectors can cause a fuel leak, leading to a fire hazard and potential engine damage.
symptoms: Fuel leak
engine malfunction
reduced engine performance.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear brakes can cause reduced stopping power, leading to increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: Rear brakes do not function properly
reduced stopping power.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the power door locks can cause inconvenience and potential safety risks, especially if the doors do not unlock in an emergency situation.
symptoms: Power door locks do not function correctly
rear doors do not unlock/lock fully.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The high idle speed issue can cause the vehicle to accelerate unexpectedly, leading to loss of control, accidents, or injuries.
symptoms: The engine idles at a high speed
the vehicle accelerates unexpectedly
the minimum speed in 1st gear is 25-30mph
the issue clears after reaching full operating temperature at 60+ mph (20 minutes).

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: An engine compartment fire can cause significant damage to the vehicle, potentially leading to a complete loss of the vehicle, and may also pose a risk to the safety of the occupants and bystanders.
symptoms: Smoke coming from under the hood
flames visible when opening the hood
burning smell
melting of plastic components
damage to the engine compartment and surrounding areas.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear axle beam can cause loss of vehicle control, leading to accidents, and can also result in costly repairs.
symptoms: The vehicle's rear axle beam breaks or cracks
causing uneven tire wear
vibrations
or noise while driving
and potentially leading to loss of control or difficulty steering.
